Chairman of Abuja Municipal Area Council (AMAC), Hon. Abdullahi Adamu Candido, has been honoured with the Award of Excellence for assisting the less privileged within the area council, by the Wheel of Hope Human Right Foundation. Leader of the foundation, Mr. Jide Abdula’ziz, who is also the anchor person at the Human Rights Radio Programme at the Aso Radio station, Abuja, explained that the award was necessary to encourage the workaholic chairman of AMAC in conducting the affairs of the area council. Abdula’ziz commended Candido’s sensitivity and concern towards the welfare of mankind as was exemplified when he donated the sum of N400, 000 to assist a physically challenged lady, whose one leg was amputated through medical surgery, adding that Candido listened to the Human Right programme and was touched by the lady’s plight, which made him to drive straight to the radio station, where he made the donation. Responding, the AMAC chairman, Hon. Abdullahi Adamu Candido thanked the leadership of the foundation for honouring him with the award, just as he described the Human Rights Radio Programme as the first of its kind in Abuja as far as Human Rights programme is concerned.